This particular instance is the class prototype, through this cloning process it creates 81 instances for use as actual cells

When created as a clone, it switches to the blank costume, then checks if it is the last cell in the row. It then iterates its cell and row numbers accordingly to create the next clone, unless it is row9cell9, in which case it informs the program that all cells are in place (doneLoading)
Makes the cell blank, then sets its position according to its row and column numbers. When the program is solving, it reflects all changes made in the grid list
When not solving, whenever a cell is clicked on, it allows a user to input a number. If it passes input check, then the cell reflects the input, else it becomes empty again
